        Vector4 toHomogeneous()
        Description copied from interface: Vector
        Creates a new vector that is the homogeneous representation of this vector. The return value contains the same elements with a 1 appended to the end; e.g. for (a, b, c) it returns (a, b, c, 1).
        Specified by:

      • fromHomogeneous

        Vector2 fromHomogeneous()
        Description copied from interface: Vector
        Assuming this vector is in homogeneous form, returns the Cartesian representation. This function performs homogeneous division, and e.g. for (a, b, c, d) it returns (a/d, b/d, c/d).
        Specified by:
        fromHomogeneous in interface Vector
        Returns:
        the Cartesian representation of this vector
